article.description: Kamar Baldwin had 23 points as Butler topped Wofford 80-61 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Baldwin scores 23 to lead Butler past Wofford 80-61
article.linkText: Baldwin scores 23 to lead Butler past Wofford 80-61
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Kamar Baldwin had 23 points as Butler topped Wofford 80-61 on Saturday night. Bryce Nze had 12 points for Butler (4-0), which won its fourth straight game. Sean McDermott added 10 points and seven rebounds. Aaron Thompson had seven assists. Storm Murphy had 19 points for the Terriers (2-2). Chevez Goodwin and Nathan Hoover each added 12 points. Butler matches up against Morehead State at home on Friday. Wofford matches up against Missouri on the road on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
